text_blocks.snippet: Prince passed away on April 21, 2016, at the age of 57.
Prince was a legendary multi-instrumentalist known for performing nearly all instruments on his studio recordings. His core professional roles included:

list.snippet: Occupations: Singer-songwriter, record producer, musician, dancer, actor, film director, and studio engineer.
Vocals: Renowned for a wide vocal range, featuring a far-reaching falsetto, baritone registers, and high-pitched screams.
Guitar: Considered a virtuoso; proficient in funk, rock, blues, and jazz styles.
Keyboards/Piano: Mastered early in life; integrated complex chords and innovative synthesizer sounds into the "Minneapolis Sound".
Drums/Percussion: Skilled in intricate, complex funk-influenced drumming; also a pioneer in the use of drum machines.
Bass Guitar: Played distinctive and inventive bass lines on many of his own recordings.

text_blocks.snippet: On his debut album, For You, Prince was credited with playing 27 different instruments. While he was a master of the core rhythm section (guitar, bass, drums, keyboards), he was also proficient in:

list.snippet: Strings/Wind: Saxophone, flute, harmonica, and reportedly violin and trumpet.
Percussion: Congas, bongos, timbales, finger cymbals, and tambourine.

text_blocks.snippet: At the time of his death, Prince's primary residence and creative headquarters was Paisley Park.

references.title: Prince June 7, 1958 – April 21, 2016 ❤️ 🎶 🎵 Singer, songwriter, musician, and actor. Regarded as one of the most influential musicians of his generation, Prince was known for his flamboyant, androgynous persona, wide vocal range, which included a far-reaching falsetto and high-pitched screams, as well as his skill as a multi-instrumentalist, often preferring to play all or most of the instruments on his recordings. His music incorporated a wide variety of styles, including funk, R\u0026B, rock, new wave, soul, synth-pop, pop, jazz, blues, and hip hop. Prince produced his albums himself, pioneering the Minneapolis sound. Prince has sold more than 100 million records worldwide, ranking him among the best-selling music artists of all time.[19] His awards include the Grammy President's Merit Award, the American Music Awards for Achievement and of Merit, the Billboard Icon Award, an Academy Award, and a Golden Globe Award. He was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 2004, the UK Music Hall of Fame in 2006, and the Rhythm and Blues Music Hall of Fame in 2016, and was inducted twice into the Black Music \u0026 Entertainment Walk of Fame in 2022.
